                <h2>About Livestock Ranching</h2>
                <p>Livestock ranching is an extensive agricultural system focused on raising grazing animals such as cattle, sheep, goats, or horses on large areas of land called ranches.</p>

                <h3>Key Characteristics:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Large land requirements</li>
                    <li>Low input costs per unit area</li>
                    <li>Grazing-based feeding systems</li>
                    <li>Primary products: meat, wool, hides</li>
                    <li>Common in arid and semi-arid regions</li>
                    <li>Extensive rather than intensive farming</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Common Livestock:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cattle (beef production)</li>
                    <li>Sheep (wool and meat)</li>
                    <li>Goats (milk and meat)</li>
                    <li>Horses (working animals)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
